@borisstoyanov @rhtyd @DaanHoogland 

Guys, one issue while porting this feature to 4.11 which was not present on 4.6. In this commit: https://github.com/apache/cloudstack/commit/37301ed4540450c29be4f975d58b38dbeec6c296#diff-6adc687ad4a13d4b956fdc638299401b `domain_vlan_map` is introduced. When adding a new range on domain, a new entry on `domain_vlan_map` is created. As `IpAddressManagerImpl#fetchNewPublicIp` lists non dedicated zone wide vlans, but always returns range corresponding to vlan id = 1 (as there's no entry for it on domain_vlan_map) - check `ZoneWideNonDedicatedVlanSearch` search builder on `VlanDaoImpl`.
What do you think will be the best solution for this case?
